accuracy for very long time series since a recurrent model may "forget" a useful in-
formation present in the early elements of a long time series. However, TWIESN did 
reach competitive accuracies on several long time series datasets such as reaching a 
96.8% accuracy on Meat whose time series length is equal to 448. This would suggest 
that ESNs can solve the vanishing gradient problem especially when learning from 
long time series. 
A third important characteristic is the training size of datasets and how it affects 
a DNN's performance. Table 1.6 shows the average rank for each classifier grouped 
by the train set's size. Again, ResNet and FCN still dominate with not much of a 
difference. However we found one very interesting dataset: DiatomSizeReduction.
